      • provablyNotIsa

        boolean provablyNotIsa(CycObject term,
                     CycObject collection,
                     CycObject mt)
                       throws CycConnectionException,
                              CycApiException
        Returns true if Fort TERM is provably not a instance of Fort COLLECTION, using the given microtheory. Method implementation optimised for the binary api.
        Parameters:
        term - the term
        collection - the collection
        mt - the microtheory in which the ask is performed
        Returns:
        true if Fort TERM is provably not a instance of Fort COLLECTION
        Throws:
        CycConnectionException - if cyc server host not found on the network or the Cyc server cannot be found
        CycApiException - if the api request results in a cyc server error
